Ah, that's because the debugger will fall back to an available ui_type if it can't find the ui_type specified by the user. My guess is that you don't have pyrealine installed on your Windows. You can install it with something like:

"C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\Scripts\pip.exe" install pyreadline.

body:
Ah, that's because the debugger will fall back to an available ui_type if it can't find the ui_type specified by the user. My guess is that you don't have pyrealine installed on your Windows. You can install it with something like:

```
"C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\Scripts\pip.exe" install pyreadline.
```
